      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(groups): use 'channel' wording in intro for ChatType channel (fixes #95645) (AI-assisted)",
        "body": "## What Problem This Solves\n\nFor any non-DM Mattermost conversation — including a public channel — the system-prompt intro declares *\"You are in a `<provider>` group chat.\"* even when `ChatType` is `\"channel\"`. This contradicts the authoritative inbound-meta block which reports `chat_type: \"channel\"`, causing agents to misidentify public channels as group chats and emit the wrong `chat_type` in tool arguments.\n\n## What does this PR do?\n\nUses the actual `ChatType` value to pick `\"channel\"` or `\"group chat\"` in the intro line rendered by `buildGroupChatContext`.\n\n## Related Issue\n\nFixes #95645\n\n## Type of Change\n\n- [x] Bug fix (non-breaking)\n- [x] AI-assisted (Hermes Agent)\n\n## Changes Made\n\n- `src/auto-reply/reply/groups.ts`: Added `chatTypeLabel` ternary that renders \"channel\" when `ChatType === \"channel\"`, \"group chat\" otherwise. Interpolated into the intro line.\n- `src/auto-reply/reply/groups.test.ts`: Added test verifying correct wording for both `ChatType: \"channel\"` and `ChatType: \"group\"`.\n\n## How to Test\n\n1. `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs run src/auto-reply/reply/groups.test.ts` — all 7 verifications pass\n2. `grep -n 'chatTypeLabel' src/auto-reply/reply/groups.ts` — confirms the ternary at line 242\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\n- **Behavior addressed:** The intro prose in `buildGroupChatContext` unconditionally rendered \"group chat\" for all non-DM conversations, including public channels where `ChatType` is `\"channel\"`.\n- **Environment tested:** macOS 26.4.1, Node 22, OpenClaw PR branch `fix/groups-channel-wording`\n- **Steps run after the patch:** Called `buildGroupChatContext` directly from production source via tsx with both `ChatType: \"channel\"` and `ChatType: \"group\"` parameters\n- **Evidence after fix:**\n  ```\n  $ npx tsx -e \"\n  import { buildGroupChatContext } from './src/auto-reply/reply/groups.ts';\n  const r1 = buildGroupChatContext({ sessionCtx: { ChatType: 'channel', Provider: 'mattermost' }, silentReplyPolicy: 'allow', silentToken: 'NO_REPLY' });\n  console.log('=== ChatType: channel ===');\n  console.log(r1.split('\\n')[0]);\n  const r2 = buildGroupChatContext({ sessionCtx: { ChatType: 'group', Provider: 'mattermost' }, silentReplyPolicy: 'allow', silentToken: 'NO_REPLY' });\n  console.log('=== ChatType: group ===');\n  console.log(r2.split('\\n')[0]);\n  \"\n  === ChatType: channel ===\n  You are in a Mattermost channel. Your text replies are automatically sent to this group chat.\n  === ChatType: group ===\n  You are in a Mattermost group chat. Your text replies are automatically sent to this group chat.\n  ```\n- **Observed result after fix:** The production `buildGroupChatContext` function correctly distinguishes between `ChatType: \"channel\"` (renders \"Mattermost channel\") and `ChatType: \"group\"` (renders \"Mattermost group chat\"). This is the actual prompt text sent to the LLM in production.\n- **What was not tested:** Live Mattermost channel interaction — the change is a string interpolation in a pure function exercised through the production source path; no live platform needed.\n\n## Checklist\n\n- [x] Read Contributing Guide\n- [x] Conventional Commits\n- [x] Searched for duplicates\n- [x] Only related changes\n- [x] Verification pass\n- [x] Added regression coverage\n- [x] Did NOT edit CHANGELOG.md\n- [x] AI-assisted disclosure included\n\n\n",
        "branch": "fix/mattermost-channel-intro-wording",
